Vice President Biden had a video teleconference with British Deputy Prime Minister Clegg to discuss their shared strategic agenda. They talked about Biden's recent visit to Iraq and the progress of Iraqi efforts to form a government. Clegg briefed Biden on his own visit to Afghanistan and Pakistan, where he met with leaders and visited British NATO ISAF troops in Helmand. They also discussed counterterrorism cooperation and expressed support for direct talks between Israel and Palestine. Clegg accepted Biden's invitation to meet in Washington, DC on September 23rd.